timedatectl set-ntp true

pacstrap /mnt base base-devel intel-ucode iw wireless_tools wpa_supplicant dialog linux-firmware linux-lts linux-headers linux-lts-headers

genfstab -U /mnt >> /mnt/etc/fstab

arch-chroot /mnt

ln -s /usr/share/zoneinfo/Europe/Stockholm /etc/localtime

 hwclock --systohc

Uncomment en_US.UTF-8 UTF-8 and other needed localizations in /etc/locale.gen, and generate them with:

# locale-gen

et the LANG variable in locale.conf(5) accordingly, for example:

/etc/locale.conf

LANG=en_US.UTF-8

If you set the keyboard layout, make the changes persistent in vconsole.conf(5):

/etc/vconsole.conf

KEYMAP=de-latin1

Hostname

Create the hostname(5) file with the desired hostname:

/etc/hostname

myhostname

Consider adding a matching entry to /etc/hosts:

127.0.1.1 myhostname.localdomain myhostname



